    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1961-10-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1961-10-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="265"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d265">
                <head>265. National Security Action Memorandum No. 100<note n="0" type="source"
                        xml:id="d265fn0">Source: Washington National Records Center, RG 330, <gloss
                            target="#t_OASD1">OASD</gloss> (C) A Files: <gloss target="#t_FRC1"
                            >FRC</gloss> 71 A 2896, Cuba 381 (Sensitive). Top Secret. Copies were
                        sent to the Secretary of Defense, the Director of Central Intelligence, and
                            <persName corresp="#p_GRN2">Richard Goodwin</persName>, as Director of
                        the Cuban Task Force.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1961-10-05">October 5, 1961</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="to">
                    <head>TO</head>
                    <item>The Secretary of State</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Contingency Planning for Cuba<note n="1" xml:id="d265fn1">For the nature
                            of the contingency planning required, see <ref target="#d266">Document
                                266</ref>.</note>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>In confirmation of oral instructions conveyed to Assistant Secretary of State
                        <persName corresp="#p_WRE1">Woodward</persName>, a plan is desired for the
                    indicated contingency in Cuba.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BMG2">
                            <hi rend="strong">McGeorge Bundy</hi>
                        </persName>
                        <note n="2" xml:id="d265fn2">Printed from a copy that bears this typed
                            signature.</note>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
